caption: Love the food and love the people that work here!  I was standing outside in the cold one day waiting for my food, and the guy making my pita was kind enough to give me a warm falafel to apologize for the long wait.  Made my evening!  This place is delicious, open late, and a Central Sq staple!

I don't kniw what happened recently, or they did change the personal, but the service is not the same. I did an order #253848141, the chicken wad cut roughly, big pieces of it, not like usual. And I asked for garlic sauce, I got another tyoe of sauce that I threw away!! They were better before. I give 2* because the taste was there, otherwise 1 star. Really disappointed.
Good food, good portions and very affordable prices. Very much recommended
When the falafel is green in the middle, it is done right.  This place is very authentic and welcoming.  Be ready to takeout- it’s a tight space.  Great Central Square institution.
Rude stuff

Finally gooood falafel in Boston! I’m from Beirut and have been on the hunt for a good falafel sandwich here since 7 years! Went to every highly rated shop. Mostly bells and whistles with the actual falafel barely edible. Came to this place because of the street-food feel. The guy gave us complimentary lentil soup (also home-made feel) while we waited in the cold. I had low expectations. I was SHOCKED when I sank my teeth into it. As good as the best falafel in Beirut down town. Sooo happy I found this place! Makes the Boston winter so much more tolerable...
Have been coming to Aleppo for years and is one of my favorite takeout places in Boston. Danny and company are super friendly and make excellent food (hummus is second to none). Highly recommended!

December update: owner threatened to spit in my food when I didn't like the freshness of the meat. What a joke this place has become.  This place is not what it used to be. Avoid. New management destroyed the quality of the food and service in this place. Update: The owner became mean and rude.
Delicious Chicken Pita
Sooo delicious!! This place never disappoints and the service is fantastic! I come here at least once a week and always have a great meal
Rude and bad attitude.  Terrible customer service. Don't know what the food tastes like because we weren't able to get past that.
Great fast service and food

Don’t even try to go to this place, service is bad, one guy working by himself doesn’t talk to you he has an attitude, when I place the order it said 15 minutes to pickup I got there and I had to wait go an other 20 minutes.... never going back

This place HITS! I can’t get enough of it! Love how it has enough vegetarian dishes to choose from! Even with delivery the food is always fresh and delicious, and well packaged. You can they care about the food they are serving with how it is prepared. It’s much appreciated!

This place is really wonderful. Everything tastes incredibly fresh, tasty, and homemade. The food is also very authentic. I have never had hummus like the hummus here-- it had the consistency of a mousse, and it was just delicious. We had their falafel, lamb shawarma, chicken shawarma, and everything was fantastic. We also talked to one of the owners while he was making our food, and he was so incredibly kind, welcoming, and generous. We're so excited to keep coming back here and supporting this great local business!
Dry and not at all tasteful. Disappointing 😔
Very very delicious 👍🏻exactly same oversees Falafel. love it

Fabulous little spot in Cambridge for fast, delicious food for all ages. Picked up the beautiful Balela with chicken (shawarma) platter & a few desserts we loved: the chocolate-walnut baklava, halawa/ halva, & the Mamoul Date (shortbread pastry stuffed with date). Super friendly service. Will go back again & again!
Quality food Long-standing Middle eastern restaurant in the heart of Central Square
Awesome bread!
All three other middle eastern restaurants in the area are better.  No "niche".  Food is just ok and owner is extremely unfriendly with costumers and extremely friendly with police.
Food is very good, except for a few things that I hope they improve: their Avocado Hummus is too salty. And their menu doesn't say that Moudardara has rice mixed in the lentil dish.

The shawarma is more like a dry pita sandwich than what you’d want when you imagine shawarma. It needs more sauce and flavor. The pita itself was also cold and just bland. The service was quick and friendly, though!

This is the best Falafel place in greater Boston, hands-down. It was when it was Falafel Palace and their remodel (and ability to now take credit cards) has in no way impacted the high quality food, but given the restaurant a lovely facelift. One of my friends used to live down the street back in 2007 and was a regular (much more than I), and when we went in a couple months ago the guy behind the counter recognized him, was excited to see him, and took a picture with him.  I personally love the lamb and beef shawarma (get the hot sauce, it's not too spicy). Always soft, high-quality pita, fresh meat. My wife swears by the falafel. The service is always friendly, fast, and pleasant. I've long since moved out to the suburbs but going back for Aleppo will always be worth the drive.

BEWARE!!!!!!  AVOID THIS PLACE !!!!! Multiple Web SITES with menus and they have different prices. PREDATORY BUSINESS MODEL!! You might pay MORE THAN DOUBLE for the food if you happen on the wrong site.  Owner thinks that's the customer's problem.
Delicious and inexpensive food and the people who run the place are wonderful! The birds nests are especially incredible.

Very bad customer service . Despite having ordered on the phone they kept taking people who were coming later and did not give any explanation. Additionally they were extremely rude.  Vegetarian fare is not great. Despite this they are so rude.  Surprised they can afford to be in business, . ' Hygienic conditions not good too.   Pl save your dollars .

Best falafel in all of Cambridge! I grew up eating falafel but am usually disappointed at the falafel around Boston. Falafel here are so much tastier than anywhere else, plus the pitas they use are big and fluffy and delicious. Come here about once a week and have had some wonderful experiences with the staff - everyone is so kind and caring and is adding love and goodness to the world, one yummy sandwich at a time :)

A nice and CLEAN to-go place! I tried chicken shawarma and falafels and I liked shawarma more. I have one suggestion for the owners... If you warm up your breads before serving it, I'll become a regular customer! :)

A wonderful place for a quick bite - fast healthy delicious choice! I’m definitely coming back to try out all kinds of deserts that they have. The staff is absolutely amazing. Best falafel I’ve tried in Boston so far
Most legit Middle Eastern food on the side of the ocean.
went today , love it thank you ,def will be back

The service was fine for me. The shawarma was good, just the chicken was a little dry in my opinion. I think even the price could be decreased by 60¢-$1.00 The shop was clean which was nice. Inside there is only standing room, so it'd be a bit tight to stay and eat. I'd most likely go back again to try something else on the menu. I also had a seminola cake soaked in syrup. It was decent. I wouldn't get it again as it was overly sweet and more on the hard side than chewy.
Delicious Shawarma!!!
Life changing shawarma pitas! So fresh and flavorful inside. Bomb spicy sauce upon request... my go to place whenever I'm in the area.
The food is very good. Their business practice not so much. They offer deals on the menu but when you go to pay they charge you full price on everything.
Great stop in central square!

We ordered lamb and beef shawerma and it was cold. Instead of meat, we got chewy rubber in the sandwiches. That was the worst meat I've had in the states. I would choose big Mac over this sandwich if I were to die of hunger.
Great falafel
The best shawarma around, and very convenient hours!
The manager should talk to that lady She is  so rude and disrespectful I was so disappointed

Granted I ordered through Grubhub at 12:30am after working all night — I didn’t expect the food to taste AMAZING because it’s so late, but the food just tasted ... gross? The grape leaves tasted yuck and the spinach pie was weirdly spiced and so so. I’m not one for bad reviews — seriously, I’m a server so I get food, but $40 later I’m pretty disappointed. Probably will go with Taboosh or Azama next time. Sorry!! I hate bad reviews but the food was not good.
Good place to eat Middle Eastern food, Falafel will taste better if you heated it before serving
Desserts are great. Dinners are overpriced and not enough food. I would not buy takeout there except desserts.
Just had a couple of shawarmas — delicious! The people were super kind too. We’ll be back!
Falafel pita was really good. Service was really quick and price wasn't bad.
Food very healthy staff friendly and understanding
Falafel Classic is awesome.  Will be coming back.
Food was pretty good. A little overpriced and the pita is not homemade

Probably the closest to authentic shawarma i had in boston is this. There is many many shawarma places around but this was so far the one i like most. Portion size is big. The sides were generous and flavourful.
I got the lamb sharwarma. It was dry and tough. Also not too attentive.

MUST GOOOOOO! Always smells SOOOOO good in here. You have to try it. Fresh food, balanced plates and bomb roll ups! Staff is always friendly and ready to help you. Specialty vibe you won't soon forget.  If you live or work near central sq, check this spot out. Small but delicious. Clean fare and fair prices.  5 star all the way!
I felt like I was right on the Mediterranean upon my first bite of this fine cuisine.
Amazing shawarma! The pita bread is on point! Everything is fresh quality ingredients and the taste is truly Mediterranean!!
Not that good
loved this place SO much!!!!! the lamb shawarma was amazing 👍🏼👍🏼
Great food
Classic falafel 🥙 pita was delicious
I have been eating at falafel place, for at least 15 years. The food is always good. 👍
Freshly Cooked! Love it.
Amazing falafel and great service!
Updated spot in the same location as the legendary Moody's Felafel Palace.   Tasty ME fare and great cookies.

Our first visit in many months and we feel it has improved now that it has reopened as Aleppo Palace.  Good quality ingredients, friendly service, delicious food.  We had fresh falafel,  excellent shwarma, and were happy to see muhamara on the menu.  Muhamara is pretty spicy so be prepared.  I don't normally like halawa but tried the pistachio halawa which tasted great.
Bad customer service Greasy food no good
So delicious! Vegetarian and vegan friendly, truly stand out, and I’ve been around the block re: middle eastern fare. Friendly staff, delicious food, can’t say enough good things!!

Just came back (twice in the past two days) after a 2 year hiatus due to the past decline in quality. Meat spits are back up and prices are very reasonable (I've done the 2 meat pitas for 14 dollar special). Tasty. I hope they keep it up. Only issue is the space inside is nonexistent and person flow is not ideal (you can't see what is being put in your sandwich without running into the person in front of you paying).
Delicious! A no-frills excellent place to get cheap food. Ingredients are fresh and food is great. This is a great place to go after a night out in Central.

The place reopened and yes, they just got cited again for a whole bunch of violations. But the falafel sandwich is the best in the region, in my opinion. The bread pockets are fresh and fluffy, and the filling has just the right balance of spices. I have not had better falafel during all my travels in the middle east.
Far better than the old place that was there. This one's super clean, healthy, in and out without hassles... Love love love the food and will go there every day for my lunch break.
Great people, flavorful and refreshing classic dishes, with some other more innovative / unique offerings. Killer falafel.

Best Falafel Place in Boston!!! Lot of variety for vegans, fresh food, they have the best beef shawarma !!! I tried many many middle eastern places in Boston And you have everything in this place , good food, good service, open late everyday!! And they add breakfast menu which is perfect !

The falafel and shawarma are by far the best I've had in Boston. The new chef or management is killing it. The pita is delicious and the salad is fresh and crisp with really good pickles and a solid hot sauce.
Place is closed right now. Looks like construction but there's also a C rating flier so could be because of that.

What can I say about Moody’s? Solid falafel right in Central Square. They are open late, take credit card, and hand you a super long falafel wrap. It will be a good day when you grab Moody’s to go. It is very small inside, so if it is nice out I’d recommend taking your wrap to a park- Sennott Park is pretty close, or Franklin Street Park is quiet and nearby as well.
This place is never open when I need to go here.

Okay American-style Levant cuisine in a small, unassuming space. Mostly for takeout. Due to its long history and the fact that it occupies very distinctive White Castle building, Moody's has become something of a local institution.

I can’t say it’s the best falafel place but I would be unjust if I say it’s a bad one. It has decent options, fair prices and a great location. I’d recommend the falafel and the soups instead of the meaty options. It is open till late, staff is usually friendly. I think the credit card extra cost is a minor thing, you wouldn’t even care about 60 cents unless they told you. I had falafel more than 5 times here and it was always good.

low quality; they nickle and dime you. using a credit card costs $.60 extra. who carries cash these days? they need to seriously rethink their enterprise. would be happy to pay for better quality. I live in the neighborhood and lived in the middle east and wanted to really like this place, but I stopped trying because it just doesn't seem like they care about the food.
Why you misleading people with different prices on website than actual prices in store,horrible experience,paying over $10 for a small wrap is so expensive, it should loaded at least with vegetables.
The worts falafel I ever had. The food is stale and I will give it a ZERO rating if that was an option. The worst place to go for falafel, salad, and baba ganoush. Please don't go to this place!!!
Great Falafel for a quick bite.
Always good late night after drinks
Got a falafel verde wrap, cheap and awesome choice with some avocado tahini sauce.

Always works well as a late-night after-party food binge stop. I ordered the Beiruti chicken which is like a shawarma with falafel and other Mediterranean fillings and can be had in either a wrap (roll-up as they call it) or a plate. Also equipped with assorted beverages and coffee. Standing room only, so this is just a take-out.
Good, cheap, and flavorful, but had some bad meat.
Best falafel i ever had in this city
Pretty tasty little place, open until 3am. Very little seating (3 chairs), so plan on taking it with you.
Excellent middle eastern food. Freshly prepared and affordable. Very friendly
It's okay. Good for late night food
Food is decent, not great. I like that they grill the outside of the wraps and the meat is really good. They forgot half my order and took hours to fulfill the whole thing.
Really good food and not expensive. There is seeing for three in the shop
Ok tasting overpriced shawarma

One of the worst falafel I've had in my life. This place is terrible.  Falafel was dry and tasteless, beans were very bad and hummus was nothing special. Overpriced for a terrible lunch.  I have been eating middle eastern food for years and absolutely love it. Eating at this place was a HUGE mistake.
Love there spicy falafel wraps
I absolutely love their food it's so fresh and healthy for years. The people that work there are super nice.
Spicing is on point, old lady is super friendly, hot sauce is extremely legit, pitas are a little chewy. Falafel with avocado tahini and hot sauce is worth every penny.
Worst food experience and customer services ever. They don't have those tasty swarmas anymore.
the Food is good, but the guy who works there is so creepy and disrespectful... I have never seeing a guy disrespect his customers like him...
The triple veggie roll-up is where it's at.
Yummy falafel rolls with mint yogurt and a lovely owner who cooks them with love!
moodys an institution

I love Moody's! This is my go-to place for mediterranean food. It's open late, which is a huge plus in the Cambridge/Boston area, and the food is delicious. I'm a huge fan of the grape leaves and baba ganoush. It's also located in a really interesting space--it used to be a White Tower Hamburger restaurant, which was one of the early hamburger chains--they have a description of it hanging on their wall. Yay history!
It's the best mediterranean restaurant ever. The owner is very kind and funny guy, and the Beiruty sandwich its amazing.

Still delicious and fragrant falafel and open at absurdly late hours, but it's not been the same since the renovations. Some of the old combos are gone, the falafel is smaller, and the Syrian salad has ordinary cukes instead of Persian cucumbers. Sigh!
The food is always good and tasty.  It's a quality for low money.
I grew up in the middle east, and I assure you this is authentic Syrian/Lebanese Fallafel house.  Don't miss the arabic coffee and walnut cookies.
A little pricey, as other reviews have said, but always tasty and the staff are happy to change up parts of your order if you want. I've never had anything but great service.

Just got the King Shawarma Plate and the Palace Super Veggie Plate for dinner. The service was fantastic - super fast, efficient and friendly. The food was delicious - the hummus was creamy and the chicken on the King Shawarma plate was super tender and flavorful. I definitely need to get the chicken again. The portions were very generous for the price of them, and the variety of salads and sides in the portions made for a delicious mix of flavors and textures - and it was so colorful!  Also, the Syrian bread is the best Mediterranean bread I've had in Boston - it was soft, spongy, sweet, and absolutely delicious. Definitely would recommend heating it up in a toaster or oven before hand!  Thank you Moody's for a wonderful meal! Look forward to my next visit.
Can be better
Great food and one of the few places to go for a 2 am snack
Good food, but they are horrible at listening when you ask them to not put something on an order. It's happened like 3 times now.
Great food, great owners, great place,  and affordable!
Consistently one of the best falafel in town.
Slightly pricy. Great combination roll ups. Get the Allepo roll up.
Smells amazing, super friendly front of house and quick service.
Phenomenally I flavorful falafel, also made me a bit sick afterwards. The shop owner seemed nice to be honest, but the food just didn't deliver...
A must visit place.

I went for the first time today. I wasn't sure what to think bc of the reviews I had read. I went in & was greeted w a pleasant smile. They were extremely friendly & even threw in free crackers since it was my first time there. Additionally, I'm not sure what people are talking about regarding portion bc I couldn't even put a dent in my meal. I feel like the amount of food I got for the price was very fair. Food was delicious & service was extremely friendly.
Super good food and a good Chipotle alternative. Cash only though.
Used to be great a couple months ago. They just changed the menu and maybe ownership. The food was not good.
Get the King!
I'm glad they're open late night!  The falafel sandwich (roll-up) is the signature snack.  ***SOMETIMES IT'S CASH ONLY***
Always open! Well, closed once during a huge snow storm, but only after it got really bad. Decent wraps with vegetarian options.
great place for that late night snack after the bar
Took as much time as it would have taken to take my order on the phone to tell me that they didn't take orders over the phone. Lame. Went elsewhere for dinner.
after I ate my shawarma the only thing I could say was "where's the rest of it!!??" Even the poop I took afterward was tiny.

The end of an era. I've been coming here for a few years and sadly the 'new and improved' ownership/menu equals smaller portions, higher prices, and most importantly, the food is not that good anymore. A chicken plate has increased about 35% in price and the meat is bland. Acietuna in Kendall and Falafel Place in Davis are MUCH better across the board.
Tasty and consistent.  But be very clear and concise with your order, they get busy.
Excellent Falafel
Great food at a great price.  Very easy to eat gluten and/or dairy free.  Definitely a take-out place. Standing room only for eat in.
Came here after the bars were closed in the area. Good, clean place for Egyptian food. Standing room only. Tasty food.
It was my first time  I was there I didn't have enough  cash I was short  the  owner was from Syria   very nice I had a great experience Excellent Falafel  excellent hot sauce

Avoid this place. They try to milk their customers for every penny. Here are some examples:  1. They only take cash. No credit card transaction fees. Inconvenience for customers.  2. Since they only take cash, you are left with a few coins and most people just throw them into the giant tip jar they provide. More money for them!  3. Prices have been going up. Now $8.55 for a rollup!  4. Portions are smaller! I've been going here and have seen the portion size decrease by about 30%. Smaller pitas, less meat etc. You need to order two to feel full.  5. They started charging for extras like tahini sauce.
Great falafel
Baba ghanouj roll up was okay. Not the worst place in central.
Just paid you $9 for a 1/8 cup of old chicken on a pita wrap. I was done in two bites. good food, not worth the price
AMAZING! Great service, too!
They are always put of lamb
Fast
Best (and only) falafel around.
Quick bite to grab. Really great lamb

I stumbled into this place with a few buddies after having quite a few at a show in the area.  Like inebriated moths floating toward the light of their store front the smell of middle eastern spices grabbed us by the shirt collar and led us in.  We found ourself standing behind a clean glass counter inside a small building where we were promptly met with fast friendly service at an ungodly hour.  Not being familiar with the menu and being a few steps from a state of mind that would allow us to make split decisions, when asked what we wanted we simply said whatever is fast and ready to go.  The man behind the counter proceeded to throw together what I can only describe as a masterfully crafted blend of lamb, tahini, vegetables and some secrets long passed down through generations....all at a reasonable price I may add.  Point being, there isn't a soul on that trip that wouldn't consider making the hour and a half drive to Cambridge just to once again taste some of the amazing things that came out of that late night kitchen.

The food is great and delicious. But them not accepting any kind of credit or debit cards is a problem. People can't always remember to bring cash when coming to this place. Also I went there few weeks ago on a Saturday night and the guy working there was so rude and unfriendly. He was so rude and seem to not want to do anything. The food is awesome but not a friendly place.

THE WOMAN WHO SERVES THE FOOD WAS CLEANING THE COUNTER AND AROUND FOOD CONTAINER WITH A CLOTH NAPKING AND DUMPED THE FOOD BACK INTO THE FOOD CONTAINER. WHEN I SAID SOMETHING I GOT KICK OUT FROM THE RESTAURENT SAYING I HAVE BEEN RUDE.  THAT’S FOOD POISONING RIGHT THERE... I CALLED CAMBRIDGE CITY HALL INSPECTION SERVICES
Best falafel ever!
Great quick Veggie food. Simple and made mostly to take away.
Friendly staff, fast, good quality food
Whenever i get a craving for a falafel I go here, enough said.

I ordered 3 wraps to go. The guy who was filling the wraps wasn't paying attention to what he was doing. I was standing in front of him while he was talking to his friend and laughing not paying attention to what I asked him. Instead of doing lamb he was filling for chicken. The wrap was completely empty and he was about to close it up and give it to me. I asked him what is that! He told me that the owner told them not to fill the wrap. I told him "but it is almost empty!!" He said the owner doesn't care!!! I left the place without taking anything. The guy was very very ignorant and rude. And if the owner really said that so, I would never go there again and I would highly recommend against this place. As if all the shawerma places ran out of the city!!! Horrible service and horrible food.

Seriously good wraps. All of them. The meat is always succulent and never dry. The veggies and felafel are mouthwatering, and the people who work there are always pleasant. I moved to CA so I miss this place at least once a week. When I come back to Boston, I will be eating here for sure.

Extremely friendly staff/owners + great food and great portions at a reasonable price.  I walked in there randomly today for the first time and I knew immediately that it would become a fixture of my life in Cambridge.  (N.B. It's cash only.)

Fantastic food but I'm giving only 2 stars because the owner refuses to let you pay with a credit / debit card (or something like level up which is now the norm for most locations in boston or cambridge these days).
I think falafel is one of the best foods on the planet, so maybe I'm biased, but Moody's definitely doesn't disappoint. Cheap, fast, tasty. Like all good things.
Their chicken rice plate with lentil rice is delicious!

I had driven by this place for years before I finally decided to stop in on a sunny Sunday afternoon and try some food. I'm very glad I did this. I was greeted by a very happy, friendly guy (I'm guessing it must be moody? He's not moody at all!) who gave me a sample of the fried chickpea falafel. It was delicious. I've been to other "falafel" places and the actual falafel is usually pretty bland. NOT SO at Moody's there are sesame seeds and who knows what other seasoning in there but it's delicious.  So I finally ordered myself a Mr. Aleppo, which had lamb and baba ganoush. I lack the culinary vocabulary to describe the taste but I can tell you it was an explosion of sweet, savory and spice all at once and it was awesome. If you want a legit falafel, you better go here, it is hands-down the best falafel in Boston.

To begin with, this place is just OK - the food is decent (I enjoy the generous application of pickles in all of the wraps), the service is decent (if sometimes a little surly). My real beef is that they do not take credit cards. They have a machine and I could swear I have seen people using it, but they claim its for gift cards. I am typically buying $10+, and I could understand if they had a minimum, but, as it is, it is just a hassle.
good place for a quick meal. Clean and nice. Fresh veggie in the roll-up. my best falafal roll so far!

No frills, bare-bones falafel/shawarma operation that serves some of the best lamb shawarma in the Boston area. Portions of lamb, fattoush and hummus are generous, and service is quickly and friendly. They only take cash though--no credit or debit cards.

This place is perfect after leaving the bar at 2 AM and the line moves fast. I had the chicken wrap which was affordable + delicious. I would be doing falafel lovers a disservice if I said it was better than Falafel King in Downtown, though. FK takes the cake for Boston falafel!
if you want delicious falafel wraps, come here!
Falafel sandwich can be skipped in favor of the plate, don't forget to ask for hot sauce as it is not included on the plate by default.
great falafel/shawarma place. good food, great service. they've got the quick and easy meal down, and it's better for you than most fast food.

Who can resist a large, vertical rotisserie that's roasting delectable meat that's been marinating for hours? (Answer: Nobody -- that's who). On any given weekend-night, there's a high probability that drunkards in Central Square have stopped by to satisfy a craving. Open until 3am every Thursday through Saturday. Good news -- it's much healthier than the pizza that you almost ate before arriving here. Warning: Cash-only! Highlights: Chicken/Lamb Schwarma Roll-Up w/Hot Sauce, Baba Ghanouj.

I come here for the tasty lamb shwarma, freshly cooked, and nicely greasy.  Of course, it's not filet mignon (you sometimes hit gristle) and the lettuce is iceberg, but it's nicely spiced and satisfying.  Very cheap and filling... and open very late at night.
Cheap, tasty falafal. Open late.

A Central Square staple! It's open late!! A quick walk from the T. They just renovated everything. The food is good and is a good value. I love the hummus and falafel. We always get it to-go. I can't remember if they have any seats, but they may have a few.
Veggie sampler platter is a steal. Tons of baba ghanouj, hummus, tabouli and falafel for <$8.
Good falafel
Cheap & tasty

This place falls victim to the common falafel place fallacy: Serving limp green salad as a side and as a main, an insufficiently spicy falafel. If your customers can't handle the heat, don't settle for the lowest common determinator.
